    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense enters today with **Drake Baldwin** (71.77) and **Kyle Tucker** (70.74) headlining our lineup as the only two hitters cracking the 70-point threshold. **Drake Baldwin** draws a favorable matchup against Freeland, benefiting from a soft SP_xERA of 4.27 and an optimal batting position in the two-hole, which significantly inflates his run-scoring probability. Meanwhile, **Kyle Tucker** remains a foundational anchor; despite a park factor penalty, his matchup against May is neutralized by his elite profile, making him a locked-in start for production across all 5x5 categories. **Josh Lowe** also emerges as a high-upside play at 64.99; while he faces a slight efficiency drag due to the opposing catcher's pop time, his dynamic platoon advantage against right-handed pitching keeps him firmly in the \"Strong\" start tier, serving as a critical source for our scarce stolen base category.\n\nOur most difficult decision occurred at the fringe of the bench, where **Coby Mayo** (51.74) narrowly missed the final slot in our UTIL spot. Despite a solid projection driven by a favorable park and platoon edge against Fried, he ultimately lacked the efficiency floor provided by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (53.50). While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faces a daunting matchup against Ryan\u2014who boasts a sharp 3.39 xERA\u2014his elite raw talent and current xwOBA (0.386) provide a higher ceiling for counting stats than **Coby Mayo** could guarantee. Managers should remain alert regarding **Heliot Ramos**, whose score of 51.70 is marginally safer but susceptible to fluctuations; if weather reports indicate increased wind resistance in his matchup against Matz, his efficiency could dip toward our bench threshold. We are monitoring **Jordan Westburg** closely, but he remains unavailable on the IL, leaving no immediate need to shuffle the lineup for today's slate.",
